								"paragraphTitle": "NOMADS",
								"paragraphSubtitles": ["in Mongolia"],
								"paragraphContents": ["Mongolia is a large country in Asia, north of China and south of Russia. There’s a lot of space, about 1.56 million km2, but there aren’t a lot of people. There are about 3,000,000 (three million) people in Mongolia and many of these people are nomads."]
							},
							{
								"paragraphOrdinal": 2,
								"paragraphTitle": null,
								"paragraphSubtitles": null,
								"paragraphContents": ["Nomads are people who go to different places in different months or seasons. They don’t live in cities, they live in the countryside."]
							},
							{
								"paragraphOrdinal": 3,
								"paragraphTitle": null,
								"paragraphSubtitles": null,
								"paragraphContents": ["No, they don’t. They don’t have houses, but they have tents, called gers, and they have horses and other animals."]
							},
							{
								"paragraphOrdinal": 4,
								"paragraphTitle": null,
								"paragraphSubtitles": null,
								"paragraphContents": ["Some nomads move thirty times a year, some move four times a year. Many nomads go to a different place in the spring and in the fall. In Mongolia, spring is March, April and May, and fall is September and October."]
							},
							{
								"paragraphOrdinal": 5,
								"paragraphTitle": null,
								"paragraphSubtitles": null,
								"paragraphContents": ["In the spring, they go close to a river for water. In the fall, they go to the hills."]
